category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
With Stockholm Language Exchange, improve your conversational language level and ability!

We have regular meetings set up for Swedish, English, French, Spanish, German, Russian, Portuguese, Italian, Finnish, Arabic, Chinese and Japanese and more languages to come.

Thanks to all our volunteers who give up their time to help - everybody can help out in his/her mother language - , the group became a wonderful language exchange.

Below you will have an idea of the schedule. This planning can change every week, please check the calendar to see the real events and to be able to sign in:

Monday: Japanese, Swedish <br> Tuesday: English <br> Wednesday: French, German, Russian, Finnish, Swedish <br> Thursday: Spanish <br> Sunday: French, Spanish, German, Italian, Portuguese, Arabic, Chinese, Swedish

Come and improve your fluency with help of native speakers, and take actively part of the group in helping yourself people who want to learn your language!

Swedish courses Stockholm

Andy your main organiser


Jonas Rognon - Co-organiser

The groups motto is to enjoy Stockholm and every great thing about it, sharing that joy with other friends, old and new.

description:
Welcome to Stockholm Erlang Meetup - situated in Erlang Valley in Sweden, where Erlang was invented.

About this group

Founded in 2012, this community is devoted to the Erlang Ecosystem and promoting anything on the BEAM. Are you Erlang curious? You are welcome!

About Erlang

Erlang is a functional programming language created at Ericsson, and designed to build massive, distributed, resilient, scalable software. The Erlang ecosystem contains a range of supported languages (Erlang, Efene, Lua, Prolog, Elixir, LFE ...) which interact seamlessly with the OTP libraries and the BEAM VM.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
La French connexion de Stockholm regroupe les Français, francophones et francophiles habitant le grand Stockholm. Nous organisons régulièrement des rencontres, à raison d’un ”fika” dans l’après-midi chaque premier samedi du mois et un afterwork en soirée en milieu de mois. Les rencontres se font en général dans des cafés ou des bars. Il arrive que nous organisions des événements plus ponctuels (repas de Noël, tournoi de ”kubb”, excursions dans l’archipel, ou à Uppsala pour rencontrer les Français uppsaliens).


Le groupe existe depuis de nombreuses années sur le forum Photo-Suède et le groupe meetup a été créé pour faciliter l’organisation des événements. Le but du groupe est de faire se rencontrer des nouveaux venus et des ”vétérans” pour échanger sur la vie en Suède. Nous ne proposons pas d’introduction formelle, la vie de ce groupe est basée sur le volontariat, la disponibilité et la participation de tout un chacun. Les administrateurs vous encouragent tous à participer aux rencontres mais n’hésitez pas non plus à proposer vous-mêmes des activités. Les nouvelles idées sont toujours les bienvenues !

Si vous souhaitez participer à un évenement, inscrivez-vous en répondant ”Oui” et essayez de venir au rendez-vous à peu près à l’heure. Ceux qui répondent ”Peut-être” sont conviés à confirmer dès que possible s’ils viennent ou non. C’est toujours plus facile de planifier quand on sait à peu près combien de personnes vont venir. Ce sont des règles de convivialité simples, merci de les respecter ! Bienvenue à tous à la French connection !
name: French Connection Stockholm

description:
Hi!
The association Un Petit Coin de France has been founded in 2008 by a group od friends playing card games in the basement of the Stockolm's reformed church. Six years later, the association has grown a lot.
Our goal today is to share good times all year long around the French and Swedish cultures and traditions. This year, many events are scheduled: musical quiz, tastings of French and Swedish products, a Beaujolais evening and many other surprises...
For those who loves sports, it is also possible to join one of our team (innebandy or touch). For more information please check the Facebook page (https://www.facebook.com/UnPetitCoinDeFrance/).

The annual fee to be a member of the association is 100 sek and gives you access to all the activities (evenings and trainings).

Welcome!

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hej,

Vad kul att ni är intresserad av vår språkgrupp!

Den här gruppen är till för alla som vill mötas och konversera på japanska och svenska. Alla som kan hålla en konversation på grund-/medelnivå är välkomna. Är ditt modersmål svenska eller japanska och du är intresserad av att lära dig ett av språken är du också välkommen. Nybörjare i båda språken är såklart också välkomna i mån av plats (skicka ett meddelande innan du blir medlem om du är osäker på din nivå).

Vi talar japanska i en timme och sedan byter vi till svenska den återstående timmen.

☆Schema

18:00〜19:00 Japanska

19:00〜20:00 Svenska

Har ni några synpunkter, idéer eller andra förslag skicka gärna ett meddelande så löser vi det.

Vi ses snart~

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br> <br>こんにちは、

このグループの目的は、日本語とスウェーデン語で語学交換することです。参加対象は、日本語ネイティヴ、スウェーデン語ネイティヴもしくは、日本語かスウェーデン語を 中級レベルで会話できる方です。 

 もちろん、スウェーデン語初心者もしくは日本語初心者の方も大歓迎です。

毎週カフェやバーに集まり、1時間日本語を話し、残りの1時間はスウェーデン語に切り替えます。

開催場所は固定ではありません。みんなで行ってみたいカフェやバーがあればどんどん教えてください。語学交換以外にも、一緒に料理をするだとか博物館に行くといった文化交流イベントも大歓迎です。みんなでやってみたいことがあれば、どしどし提案してください。

また、そのほか質問や改善点があれば遠慮なく言ってください。

みなさんが、来てよかったな〜来週も来たいな！と思えるようなミートアップグループにできるよう一緒に頑張りましょうね。

☆スケジュール

18：00〜19：00日本語

19：00〜20：00スウェーデン語

それではまた。

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br>

Hello,

How great that you're interested in our meetup group! <br>

The aim of this group is to converse in Japanese and Swedish. Everybody who can hold a conversation at an intermediate level is welcome to this meetup. If your mother tongue is Japanese or Swedish and you're interested in learning the other language, you're welcome to join as well. Beginners in both languages are also welcome based on how many spots are available (if you're uncertain about your current level send us a message before applying to the group). <br>

We speak Japanese for 1 hour and then we switch to Swedish for the remaining hour.

☆Schedule

18:00〜19:00 Japanese

19:00〜20:00 Swedish

If you have any viewpoints, ideas or other proposals please send a message and we'll try to incorporate it. <br>

See you there~ <br>
name: Speak Japanese and Swedish/Prata japanska och svenska

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Obs! Den här gruppen tar en paus för tillfället då jag är i Thailand. Jag är tillbaka i juni 2018 :)

Sawadii khap!

Thailändska ska man förstås helst lära sig från någon som har thailändska som modersmål, men ibland kan det vara värdefullt att också diskutera språket med någon som har ett svenskt perspektiv. Någon som redan har gått igenom samma inlärningsprocess i vuxen ålder och kan dela med sig av sina erfarenheter.

Denna meetup-grupp är till för dig som vill lära dig de absoluta grunderna i thailändska. Vilka ljud finns i thailändska som vi inte har i svenska språket? Hur fungerar det thailändska skriftspråket och är det värt att lära sig det? Vilka ord och fraser är viktigast att lära sig först?

Jag som har skapat gruppen har åkt till Thailand regelbundet i över 10 år. Jag kan inte thailändska flytande, men jag behärskar grunderna väldigt bra. Lektionerna är gratis och är något som jag tänker mig att vi utformar lite tillsammans utifrån vad deltagarna har för önskemål. Likaså skulle jag vilja ha förslag på var vi kan hålla till. Jag är van vid att ha meetups på restauranger och caféer, men det är viktigt att man kan sitta lite separat så man inte stör de andra gästerna.

/Adam
name: Thailändska för nybörjare
organizer.name: Adam Nybäck

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hallo alle zusammen und herzlich willkommen auf den Stockholm German Meetup!
Das Ziel dieses Meetup ist Konversation auf Deutsch zu betreiben, um unsere Sprachkenntnisse zu verbessern. Selbstverständlich sind deutsche Muttersprachler auch willkommen :)

Wer bin ich? Ich komme aus Italien aber wohne in Stockholm seit fast einem Jahr. Ich arbeite im Vertrieb und habe vorher mit deutschen Kunden gearbeitet. Ich habe German Meetups in Budapest und Dublin organisiert. Ich arbeite echt viel unter der Woche, deswegen habe ich mich entscheidet, ein Meetup am Wochenende zu organisieren.
Vorher konnte ich Deutsch fliessend sprechen, jetzt muss ich es aber aufpolieren :)

Alle, die genug Deutsch kennen, um ein bisschen Konversation zu machen, sind einfach willkommen.

LG,

Stefania

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
To know if you should join, you need to know the reason for why I started this group: I’m a Swedish/Indian woman who spent most my life in international and expatriate surroundings. I’m since 3 years back in my beloved hometown, but at the same time lost. I’m in a steady relationship but not interested in family-life (children)... or the next night out for that matter (although very appreciated now and then). I want to find other women with some kind of connection to Scandinavia, who also are “stuck” between social cultures (returned Swedish expats, foreign parents but Swedish themselves, moved to Sweden and changed citizenship, you get the idea), who together with me want to find more people who we can laugh, explore, and enjoy some of our free time with.

What makes this group a little different is that everyone is made into an Event Organiser, and thereby can, if they want to, create their own "event" or activity. The level of effort and prestige the event is worth is decided by each Even Organiser. For myself it's zero prestige and minimum effort and so far I've had loads of fun with it!
name: Scandinavian women with expat/foreign backgrounds

description:
Welcome to all those who are interested in practising English conversation and improving English language skills!

Currently we have one weekly session to practise speaking English at an intermediate level. We discuss general topics but have some emphasis on learning and discussing new words, phrases and idioms as they come up. Each week we publish online a summary of the material that we cover.

If your English is intermediate or better and you'd like a chance to engage in lively conversation, ask questions and maybe learn something new, then this session is for you.

If you are interested in beginners or improvers English, please let us know. We may set up other weekly sessions if there is sufficient demand.

description:
Welcome to the Sunday group for intermediate italian level . This is a casual conversation group where people who want to improve their italian can come, chat and have a coffee (or another beverage, if you desire). We don't set topic or structure to the meeting aside from coming to the cafe and chatting about whatever's on your mind.

Advanced and native speakers are also welcome to come and help out. It should be noted that helpers are not expected to be teachers, however, if you have some questions I'm sure they will be more than willing to try to help you out.

Please be considerate to other members by keeping your RSVPs up to date and attending events when you indicate that you will.

If you're on the waiting list, please check your status in case you've been moved up to the Attendees list. <br>*** WARNING: pickpockets *** <br>Phones, laptops and wallets have been stolen in the Cafés in Down town . Gamla Stan , Down town and cafes are the paradise for pickpockets, so please watch your stuff (even in the pockets of your jackets that hang on your seat)! <br>**************

Hej alla koreaintresserade! :)

Målet med den här gruppen är att bli en mötesplats för koreaintresserad svenskar och inflyttade koreaner som vill träffas och mingla och samtidigt öva på svenska/koreanska. Vi har inga planerade lektioner eller likande, utan vi träffas och fikar och pratar helt enkelt.

Alla nivåer är välkomna. Skriv bara vilken nivå du är på så att vi kan hitta någon som passar bra till din språknivå. Vi ses!

Minjeong & Osvald

(This group is mainly for people who are fluent in either Swedish or Korean to get a good language exchange.)

안녕하세요! :)

스웨덴에 거주중인 한국분들과 한국에 관심이 많은 스웨덴분들이 정기적으로 서로 만나 교류하고 스웨덴어/한국어를 연습할 수 있도록 언어교환 모임을 시작해보려고 합니다. 본 모임에서 언어수업 등을 제공하는 것은 아니나, 새로운 사람을 만나 이야기 나누것을 좋아하는 분, 스웨덴어를 연습하고자 하는 분은 모두 환영입니다. 각 레벨에 맞는 대화 파트너를 찾아드릴 수 있게 신청시에 본인의 스웨덴어 레벨을 적어주세요.
그럼 모임에서 뵙겠습니다 :)

민정&오스발드 드림

description:
Meet other Expats,Danes and International English speaking people in Denmark,enjoy great fun events several times a month and have a open debate on whatever is on your mind. You can suggest Events and ,If you become a assitant organizer ,you can post Events yourself!Events must be open to everyone! You can post about politics,religion,give good tips and answer questions from newcomers to Denmark on where and what is the best way to do whatever they might want to know about in short you can post just about anything and ask for any information!Expect a reply to your comments and questions.Ask about anything from where is the best of whatever to the worst of what ever or ask about travel tips,ASK ABOUT EVERYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW! Racial slurs and personel attacks on board members are a no no and if a person disagrees with you please do not label them as conservative,liberal etc. Unless they describe themselves as such.
So please feel free to join, post away on the message board and become a assitant organizer if you wish so we can build a great network of interesting people!

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
The aim of this group is to bring together people who have an interest in, and curiosity about the Middle East, regardless of ethnicity, cultural, religious or political background. 

Our vision is to  build a welcoming, tolerant and inclusive community, where we get to share and celebrate the richness and diversity of the various cultures of the Middle East, and at the same time, learn about, and from other cultures of the world.

The activities and events we attend together have Middle Eastern cultural hallmarks and include: Watching movies, dining out, concerts, art & photo exhibitions, dinner parties, language classes, museum visits, literary evenings and more.

Reviews & Facebook Page:

Please check out the many great reviews of the group here
You can also follow us on out Facebook Page for regular bite-size information about the region. 

Membership:

A a one-off, obligatory membership fee of 50 kr. is required upon joining this group to help cover the expenses associated with running the group.  This fee gives you the choice to attend ALL events & activities arranged/ advertised on this meetup page, the opportunity to meet new interesting people, make new friends, and build your network, while in Copenhagen.

 We look forward to having you among us:)
name: Middle Eastern Cultures

We are currently looking for a new location also close to Nørreport. I am hoping very very much that we will be back on again as soon as possible. **

Mundo Lingo is a sociable and completely free new way to practice another language in Copenhagen and make local friends.

Who are we? We are a group of people from all around the world, (locals and internationals) who get together for a good night, practice languages, make friends and have a nice time. 

We have flag stickers of almost every country/region which represent your spoken languages. It’s for all levels and nationalities and its completely free! 
Come check us out! facebook.com/mundolingo


Mundo Lingo er en social og gratis måde at øve sprog og møde nye mennesker på i København.

Hvem er vi? Vi er en gruppe af mennesker fra hele verden som mødes for at øve forskellige sprog, møde nye venner og nyde en god aften sammen.

Alle niveauer og nationaliteter er velkomne og det er altid gratis!

Så kom og vær' med!

Check us out on facebook: fb.com/mundolingo

Bine ati venit!

Acesta este grupul vorbitorilor de limba romana care iubesc Suedia si locuiesc in Malmö si imprejurimi. Grupul este deschis tuturor celor ce au facut din acest colt indepartat de tara noua lor casa si vor sa se conecteze cu alti romani pentru a mentine vie limba, traditiile, cultura si flacara sufletului romanesc. Daca esti nou in zona sau locuiesti aici de ceva vreme si doresti sa cunosti oameni faini la o bere/ceai/cafea/suc esti binevenit. 

Nota: Intentionam sa ne intalnim macar odata pe luna ca sa stam la o poveste. Oricine este binevenit si orice sugestii de activitati sunt primite cu placere. Am putea face drumetii, juca tenis, rummy, vizita muzee, sa mergem cu bicicleta, sa ne intrecem la karting, sa sarbatorim 1 Decembrie, etc, etc, etc...

description:
Japan Business & Culture Discussion Club is a group that provides valuable discussion and networking opportunities to all who are interested in learning about Japanese business & culture.


About the ORGANIZER

The organizer of the event, Masa K, is a graduate of full time MBA in Copenhagen Business School and internationally experienced coach, trainer and consultant in cross cultural management area.

His global career started as a Managing Director (as an expatriate) of a Japanese electric material company in Denmark where more than 10 different nationalities were employed. Under the diversified environment, he strove to enhance employees’ competency levels in order to create a competitive manufacturing entity and be able to supply highly reliable products constantly and in a timely manner to the European market.

Currently, he works as an HRD consultant in one of the leading training companies in Tokyo and endeavors to globalize clients' human resources by designing, coordinating and implementing effectively customized training programs.

Concurrently, he coaches individuals privately. Leveraging on his international exposure and experience, he supports global leaders to expand their horizons and maximize their potentials in a multi-national corporate environment.

description:
Our main mission at Host Minded is to bring like-minded hosts and guests together in an effort to support the new sharing economy and actively promote the values and interests of such a community.

We know there are plenty of people doing Airbnb in Copenhagen and we want to bring them together to discuss the challenges and rewards of doing Airbnb. We aim to build a strong community of individuals that have the same progressive mind-set as ours. We want to spar with host and guests alike so that we are ready to support legislation reforms in Copenhagen's rental market. This meet-up is for everyone that finds the idea appealing and everyone that has ever used Airbnb at least once in their lifetime.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
GIRL GONE INTERNATIONAL AT A GLANCE Global. Lifestyle. Online. Magazine. Community. Events. www.girlgoneinternational.com - check it out, join the global community for free, read our gorgeous glossy free online magazine written for, about by girls living abroad all over the world. We are a vibrant international community of female globe hoppers living, working, traveling or studying abroad. In cities all over the world we have hubs and we hold at least one main Girl Gone International event, meeting new like minded friends over a few drinks in hip venues.

Esther, Zsuzsanna and Fátima form the Copenhagen's Community Manager Team. The group is for women living 'abroad' in Copenhagen, girls who love to travel or recently returning from time overseas ("repats"). By joining GGI, you'll have an instant group of friends who are expats, just like you! GGI is in loads of cities all over the world so go to our map and discover more! Get connected into to the Girl Gone International Community! On top of girlgoneinternational.com, we post daily inspiration on Facebook, have rotating #GGI Twitter global correspondents as @GirlGoneIntl, have busy boards on Pinterest, have a "I am a Girl Gone International because" poster project on Tumblr, have weekly themed Instagram fun - simply hashtag your images #girlgi, have career focused conversation on LinkedIn and listen and collaborate on Spotify soundtracks! We are always looking for girls gone international to feature in our magazine and website and for contributors. To find out more email Girl Gone International founder Anne Scott. See you at an event soon!

What is Girl Gone International?

✈ We represent, connect and support women who live abroad

✈ Go anywhere, belong everywhere!

✈ 1000s of free events all over the world to help you meet new friends wherever you are

✈ Friendship makes our world go round! 

✈ Fast growing, friendly global and local community

✈ www.girlgoneinternational.com - sign up there to be the first to receive new GIRLGI magazine editions for free, know about GGI developments, invites to global meetups and travel, exclusive news and invitations to be featured in the magazine and more!

✈ We have a digital magazine with over 100,000 readers!

✈ Active hubs in over 100+ cities.

✈ 100 more hubs opening in 2018

✈ Over 150,000 active members
name: Copenhagen: Girl Gone International

description:
Meet other Expats,Danes and International English speaking people in Denmark,enjoy great fun events several times a month and have a open debate on whatever is on your mind. You can suggest Events and ,If you become a assitant organizer ,you can post Events yourself!Events must be open to everyone! You can post about politics,religion,give good tips and answer questions from newcomers to Denmark on where and what is the best way to do whatever they might want to know about in short you can post just about anything and ask for any information!Expect a reply to your comments and questions.Ask about anything from where is the best of whatever to the worst of what ever or ask about travel tips,ASK ABOUT EVERYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW! Racial slurs and personel attacks on board members are a no no and if a person disagrees with you please do not label them as conservative,liberal etc. Unless they describe themselves as such.
So please feel free to join, post away on the message board and become a assitant organizer if you wish so we can build a great network of interesting people!
name: Copenhagen International Expats Events And Free Forum

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
The aim of this group is to bring together people who have an interest in, and curiosity about the Middle East, regardless of ethnicity, cultural, religious or political background. 

Our vision is to  build a welcoming, tolerant and inclusive community, where we get to share and celebrate the richness and diversity of the various cultures of the Middle East, and at the same time, learn about, and from other cultures of the world.

The activities and events we attend together have Middle Eastern cultural hallmarks and include: Watching movies, dining out, concerts, art & photo exhibitions, dinner parties, language classes, museum visits, literary evenings and more.

Reviews & Facebook Page:

Please check out the many great reviews of the group here
You can also follow us on out Facebook Page for regular bite-size information about the region. 

Membership:

A a one-off, obligatory membership fee of 50 kr. is required upon joining this group to help cover the expenses associated with running the group.  This fee gives you the choice to attend ALL events & activities arranged/ advertised on this meetup page, the opportunity to meet new interesting people, make new friends, and build your network, while in Copenhagen.

 We look forward to having you among us:)
name: Middle Eastern Cultures

description:
*Current update* Klaptræet, as some of you may know, has now become SKAAL. Unfortunately we have left SKAAL as it has become quite expensive, now that they only sell ‘specialty’ beer. We are currently looking for a new location also close to Nørreport. I am hoping very very much that we will be back on again as soon as possible. **

Mundo Lingo is a sociable and completely free new way to practice another language in Copenhagen and make local friends.

Who are we? We are a group of people from all around the world, (locals and internationals) who get together for a good night, practice languages, make friends and have a nice time. 

We have flag stickers of almost every country/region which represent your spoken languages. It’s for all levels and nationalities and its completely free! 
Come check us out! facebook.com/mundolingo


Mundo Lingo er en social og gratis måde at øve sprog og møde nye mennesker på i København.

Hvem er vi? Vi er en gruppe af mennesker fra hele verden som mødes for at øve forskellige sprog, møde nye venner og nyde en god aften sammen.

Alle niveauer og nationaliteter er velkomne og det er altid gratis!

Så kom og vær' med!

Check us out on facebook: fb.com/mundolingo
name: Mundo Lingo Copenhagen - Free Language Exchange

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Bine ati venit!

Acesta este grupul vorbitorilor de limba romana care iubesc Suedia si locuiesc in Malmö si imprejurimi. Grupul este deschis tuturor celor ce au facut din acest colt indepartat de tara noua lor casa si vor sa se conecteze cu alti romani pentru a mentine vie limba, traditiile, cultura si flacara sufletului romanesc. Daca esti nou in zona sau locuiesti aici de ceva vreme si doresti sa cunosti oameni faini la o bere/ceai/cafea/suc esti binevenit. 

Nota: Intentionam sa ne intalnim macar odata pe luna ca sa stam la o poveste. Oricine este binevenit si orice sugestii de activitati sunt primite cu placere. Am putea face drumetii, juca tenis, rummy, vizita muzee, sa mergem cu bicicleta, sa ne intrecem la karting, sa sarbatorim 1 Decembrie, etc, etc, etc...
name: Romanian-speaking community in Malmö and its surroundings

description:
Japan Business & Culture Discussion Club is a group that provides valuable discussion and networking opportunities to all who are interested in learning about Japanese business & culture.


About the ORGANIZER

The organizer of the event, Masa K, is a graduate of full time MBA in Copenhagen Business School and internationally experienced coach, trainer and consultant in cross cultural management area.

His global career started as a Managing Director (as an expatriate) of a Japanese electric material company in Denmark where more than 10 different nationalities were employed. Under the diversified environment, he strove to enhance employees’ competency levels in order to create a competitive manufacturing entity and be able to supply highly reliable products constantly and in a timely manner to the European market.

Currently, he works as an HRD consultant in one of the leading training companies in Tokyo and endeavors to globalize clients' human resources by designing, coordinating and implementing effectively customized training programs.

Concurrently, he coaches individuals privately. Leveraging on his international exposure and experience, he supports global leaders to expand their horizons and maximize their potentials in a multi-national corporate environment.

Wir treffen uns jeweils am zweiten Dienstag des Monats um 19.00 im Restaurant "Spisen" (in der Nähe des Marktplatzes).

Man kann sich auch auf die E-mail-Liste der Parallelorganisation setzen lassen, dann erhält man jeweils eine E-mail, wenn wieder ein Stammtisch ansteht: ralph.schulz.lund@gmail.com

description:
Our main mission at Host Minded is to bring like-minded hosts and guests together in an effort to support the new sharing economy and actively promote the values and interests of such a community.

We know there are plenty of people doing Airbnb in Copenhagen and we want to bring them together to discuss the challenges and rewards of doing Airbnb. We aim to build a strong community of individuals that have the same progressive mind-set as ours. We want to spar with host and guests alike so that we are ready to support legislation reforms in Copenhagen's rental market. This meet-up is for everyone that finds the idea appealing and everyone that has ever used Airbnb at least once in their lifetime.

description:
GIRL GONE INTERNATIONAL AT A GLANCE Global. Lifestyle. Online. Magazine. Community. Events. www.girlgoneinternational.com - check it out, join the global community for free, read our gorgeous glossy free online magazine written for, about by girls living abroad all over the world. We are a vibrant international community of female globe hoppers living, working, traveling or studying abroad. In cities all over the world we have hubs and we hold at least one main Girl Gone International event, meeting new like minded friends over a few drinks in hip venues.

Esther, Zsuzsanna and Fátima form the Copenhagen's Community Manager Team. The group is for women living 'abroad' in Copenhagen, girls who love to travel or recently returning from time overseas ("repats"). By joining GGI, you'll have an instant group of friends who are expats, just like you! GGI is in loads of cities all over the world so go to our map and discover more! Get connected into to the Girl Gone International Community! On top of girlgoneinternational.com, we post daily inspiration on Facebook, have rotating #GGI Twitter global correspondents as @GirlGoneIntl, have busy boards on Pinterest, have a "I am a Girl Gone International because" poster project on Tumblr, have weekly themed Instagram fun - simply hashtag your images #girlgi, have career focused conversation on LinkedIn and listen and collaborate on Spotify soundtracks! We are always looking for girls gone international to feature in our magazine and website and for contributors. To find out more email Girl Gone International founder Anne Scott. See you at an event soon!

What is Girl Gone International?

✈ We represent, connect and support women who live abroad

✈ Go anywhere, belong everywhere!

✈ 1000s of free events all over the world to help you meet new friends wherever you are

✈ Friendship makes our world go round! 

✈ Fast growing, friendly global and local community

✈ www.girlgoneinternational.com - sign up there to be the first to receive new GIRLGI magazine editions for free, know about GGI developments, invites to global meetups and travel, exclusive news and invitations to be featured in the magazine and more!

✈ We have a digital magazine with over 100,000 readers!

✈ Active hubs in over 100+ cities.

✈ 100 more hubs opening in 2018

✈ Over 150,000 active members

Sinn des Stammtisches ist, die deutsche Kultur in Lund zu fördern.  Zu diesem Zwecke können sich die Mitglieder mit Gleichgesinnten bei einem Abendessen und/oder einem Bier unterhalten und so die Geselligkeit pflegen. Jeder, der Deutsch spricht, ist herzlich eingeladen.

Wir treffen uns jeweils am zweiten Dienstag des Monats um 19.00 im Restaurant "Spisen" (in der Nähe des Marktplatzes).

Man kann sich auch auf die E-mail-Liste der Parallelorganisation setzen lassen, dann erhält man jeweils eine E-mail, wenn wieder ein Stammtisch ansteht: ralph.schulz.lund@gmail.com

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Welcome to the Language & Culture Exchange meetup in Umeå!

This group is new.

If you want to talk with native speakers to learn a new language, improve your language skills, or are simply eager to discover new cultures, you have found the right place! ;)

The goal of this hub is to connect local people and people who have come to Umeå from other countries in order to help them understand each other's culture and languages while developing new friendships. Whether you are someone fond of foreign languages, a student, a recent immigrant, an employee of an international company or a world traveler, this group aims to bring together native and non-native speakers of many different languages from various countries around the world who have a passion for sharing their their culture, knowledge, language and overseas experiences while learning about others. We also want newcomers, couch-surfers and visitors to see, enjoy, and learn more about Umeå.
Any age, gender, ethnicity and social class is welcome. We will not judge you.

We meets every Monday and encourages long term friendships between members. Our members speak different languages including Swedish, English, and French. Come as you are; this is a casual meeting. Please RSVP to the event before showing up if you can, this helps us to keep track of numbers so we can plan/organize events in a better way. If you're new, just come to us and introduce yourself in a simple way.

Bring your friends: Everyone is welcome!


-----
Meetup Rules:
1) You should not be rude, aggressive, or have any socially inappropriate behaviour towards the other members.
2) You should be open-minded and tolerant. If you debate about other cultures, please do it in a nice way.
3) You should be at least 21+ for bar events. (no age limit otherwise)
4) For events in coffee places and bars, remember to please buy a drink (or two, three, or four) to support our hosts.

— We REMOVE members that break the rules. —

description:
With Stockholm Language Exchange, improve your conversational language level and ability!

We have regular meetings set up for Swedish, English, French, Spanish, German, Russian, Portuguese, Italian, Finnish, Arabic, Chinese and Japanese and more languages to come.

Thanks to all our volunteers who give up their time to help - everybody can help out in his/her mother language - , the group became a wonderful language exchange.

Below you will have an idea of the schedule. This planning can change every week, please check the calendar to see the real events and to be able to sign in:

Monday: Japanese, Swedish <br> Tuesday: English <br> Wednesday: French, German, Russian, Finnish, Swedish <br> Thursday: Spanish <br> Sunday: French, Spanish, German, Italian, Portuguese, Arabic, Chinese, Swedish

Come and improve your fluency with help of native speakers, and take actively part of the group in helping yourself people who want to learn your language!

Swedish courses Stockholm

Andy your main organiser


Jonas Rognon - Co-organiser

A group for people of all ages to highlight, invite and share the big FREE or Discounted events going on in Stockholm and meet up as groups.

These could be comedy shows, festivals, concerts, cinema premiers, opening night events, dancing and cultural events, all within our great city of Stockholm.

If you like to have fun, meet new people and make friends, you belong right here.

The groups motto is to enjoy Stockholm and every great thing about it, sharing that joy with other friends, old and new.


This group is sponsored by www.studiofotos.se the Corporate Headshot Specialist in Stockholm

description:
Welcome to Stockholm Erlang Meetup - situated in Erlang Valley in Sweden, where Erlang was invented.

About this group

Founded in 2012, this community is devoted to the Erlang Ecosystem and promoting anything on the BEAM. Are you Erlang curious? You are welcome!

About Erlang

Erlang is a functional programming language created at Ericsson, and designed to build massive, distributed, resilient, scalable software. The Erlang ecosystem contains a range of supported languages (Erlang, Efene, Lua, Prolog, Elixir, LFE ...) which interact seamlessly with the OTP libraries and the BEAM VM.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
La French connexion de Stockholm regroupe les Français, francophones et francophiles habitant le grand Stockholm. Nous organisons régulièrement des rencontres, à raison d’un ”fika” dans l’après-midi chaque premier samedi du mois et un afterwork en soirée en milieu de mois. Les rencontres se font en général dans des cafés ou des bars. Il arrive que nous organisions des événements plus ponctuels (repas de Noël, tournoi de ”kubb”, excursions dans l’archipel, ou à Uppsala pour rencontrer les Français uppsaliens).


Le groupe existe depuis de nombreuses années sur le forum Photo-Suède et le groupe meetup a été créé pour faciliter l’organisation des événements. Le but du groupe est de faire se rencontrer des nouveaux venus et des ”vétérans” pour échanger sur la vie en Suède. Nous ne proposons pas d’introduction formelle, la vie de ce groupe est basée sur le volontariat, la disponibilité et la participation de tout un chacun. Les administrateurs vous encouragent tous à participer aux rencontres mais n’hésitez pas non plus à proposer vous-mêmes des activités. Les nouvelles idées sont toujours les bienvenues !

Si vous souhaitez participer à un évenement, inscrivez-vous en répondant ”Oui” et essayez de venir au rendez-vous à peu près à l’heure. Ceux qui répondent ”Peut-être” sont conviés à confirmer dès que possible s’ils viennent ou non. C’est toujours plus facile de planifier quand on sait à peu près combien de personnes vont venir. Ce sont des règles de convivialité simples, merci de les respecter ! Bienvenue à tous à la French connection !
name: French Connection Stockholm

description:
Hi!
The association Un Petit Coin de France has been founded in 2008 by a group od friends playing card games in the basement of the Stockolm's reformed church. Six years later, the association has grown a lot.
Our goal today is to share good times all year long around the French and Swedish cultures and traditions. This year, many events are scheduled: musical quiz, tastings of French and Swedish products, a Beaujolais evening and many other surprises...
For those who loves sports, it is also possible to join one of our team (innebandy or touch). For more information please check the Facebook page (https://www.facebook.com/UnPetitCoinDeFrance/).

The annual fee to be a member of the association is 100 sek and gives you access to all the activities (evenings and trainings).

Welcome!

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hej,

Vad kul att ni är intresserad av vår språkgrupp!

Den här gruppen är till för alla som vill mötas och konversera på japanska och svenska. Alla som kan hålla en konversation på grund-/medelnivå är välkomna. Är ditt modersmål svenska eller japanska och du är intresserad av att lära dig ett av språken är du också välkommen. Nybörjare i båda språken är såklart också välkomna i mån av plats (skicka ett meddelande innan du blir medlem om du är osäker på din nivå).

Vi talar japanska i en timme och sedan byter vi till svenska den återstående timmen.

☆Schema

18:00〜19:00 Japanska

19:00〜20:00 Svenska

Har ni några synpunkter, idéer eller andra förslag skicka gärna ett meddelande så löser vi det.

Vi ses snart~

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br> <br>こんにちは、

このグループの目的は、日本語とスウェーデン語で語学交換することです。参加対象は、日本語ネイティヴ、スウェーデン語ネイティヴもしくは、日本語かスウェーデン語を 中級レベルで会話できる方です。 

 もちろん、スウェーデン語初心者もしくは日本語初心者の方も大歓迎です。

毎週カフェやバーに集まり、1時間日本語を話し、残りの1時間はスウェーデン語に切り替えます。

開催場所は固定ではありません。みんなで行ってみたいカフェやバーがあればどんどん教えてください。語学交換以外にも、一緒に料理をするだとか博物館に行くといった文化交流イベントも大歓迎です。みんなでやってみたいことがあれば、どしどし提案してください。

また、そのほか質問や改善点があれば遠慮なく言ってください。

みなさんが、来てよかったな〜来週も来たいな！と思えるようなミートアップグループにできるよう一緒に頑張りましょうね。

☆スケジュール

18：00〜19：00日本語

19：00〜20：00スウェーデン語

それではまた。

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br>

Hello,

How great that you're interested in our meetup group! <br>

The aim of this group is to converse in Japanese and Swedish. Everybody who can hold a conversation at an intermediate level is welcome to this meetup. If your mother tongue is Japanese or Swedish and you're interested in learning the other language, you're welcome to join as well. Beginners in both languages are also welcome based on how many spots are available (if you're uncertain about your current level send us a message before applying to the group). <br>

We speak Japanese for 1 hour and then we switch to Swedish for the remaining hour.

☆Schedule

18:00〜19:00 Japanese

19:00〜20:00 Swedish

If you have any viewpoints, ideas or other proposals please send a message and we'll try to incorporate it. <br>

See you there~ <br>
name: Speak Japanese and Swedish/Prata japanska och svenska

Heading to Greece for your summer vacation and you would enjoy some "småprata" with the locals? Do you already study or speak some Greek and you would like to practice more? For whatever reason, come join the group. We will be mainly speaking Greek and some auxiliary English - if it's deemed necessary. All levels are welcome.

Ελληνικά για τις διακοπές, για διασκέδαση, για γνώση. Όποιος και αν είναι ο λόγος που μαθαίνεις ελληνικά, σε αυτή την ομάδα θα μάθεις να μιλάς καλύτερα. category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Obs! Den här gruppen tar en paus för tillfället då jag är i Thailand. Jag är tillbaka i juni 2018 :)

Sawadii khap!

Thailändska ska man förstås helst lära sig från någon som har thailändska som modersmål, men ibland kan det vara värdefullt att också diskutera språket med någon som har ett svenskt perspektiv. Någon som redan har gått igenom samma inlärningsprocess i vuxen ålder och kan dela med sig av sina erfarenheter.

Denna meetup-grupp är till för dig som vill lära dig de absoluta grunderna i thailändska. Vilka ljud finns i thailändska som vi inte har i svenska språket? Hur fungerar det thailändska skriftspråket och är det värt att lära sig det? Vilka ord och fraser är viktigast att lära sig först?

Jag som har skapat gruppen har åkt till Thailand regelbundet i över 10 år. Jag kan inte thailändska flytande, men jag behärskar grunderna väldigt bra. Lektionerna är gratis och är något som jag tänker mig att vi utformar lite tillsammans utifrån vad deltagarna har för önskemål. Likaså skulle jag vilja ha förslag på var vi kan hålla till. Jag är van vid att ha meetups på restauranger och caféer, men det är viktigt att man kan sitta lite separat så man inte stör de andra gästerna.

/Adam
name: Thailändska för nybörjare
organizer.name: Adam Nybäck

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hallo alle zusammen und herzlich willkommen auf den Stockholm German Meetup!
Das Ziel dieses Meetup ist Konversation auf Deutsch zu betreiben, um unsere Sprachkenntnisse zu verbessern. Selbstverständlich sind deutsche Muttersprachler auch willkommen :)

Wer bin ich? Ich komme aus Italien aber wohne in Stockholm seit fast einem Jahr. Ich arbeite im Vertrieb und habe vorher mit deutschen Kunden gearbeitet. Ich habe German Meetups in Budapest und Dublin organisiert. Ich arbeite echt viel unter der Woche, deswegen habe ich mich entscheidet, ein Meetup am Wochenende zu organisieren.
Vorher konnte ich Deutsch fliessend sprechen, jetzt muss ich es aber aufpolieren :)

Alle, die genug Deutsch kennen, um ein bisschen Konversation zu machen, sind einfach willkommen.

LG,

Stefania

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
To know if you should join, you need to know the reason for why I started this group: I’m a Swedish/Indian woman who spent most my life in international and expatriate surroundings. I’m since 3 years back in my beloved hometown, but at the same time lost. I’m in a steady relationship but not interested in family-life (children)... or the next night out for that matter (although very appreciated now and then). I want to find other women with some kind of connection to Scandinavia, who also are “stuck” between social cultures (returned Swedish expats, foreign parents but Swedish themselves, moved to Sweden and changed citizenship, you get the idea), who together with me want to find more people who we can laugh, explore, and enjoy some of our free time with.

What makes this group a little different is that everyone is made into an Event Organiser, and thereby can, if they want to, create their own "event" or activity. The level of effort and prestige the event is worth is decided by each Even Organiser. For myself it's zero prestige and minimum effort and so far I've had loads of fun with it!
name: Scandinavian women with expat/foreign backgrounds

description:
Welcome to all those who are interested in practising English conversation and improving English language skills!

Currently we have one weekly session to practise speaking English at an intermediate level. We discuss general topics but have some emphasis on learning and discussing new words, phrases and idioms as they come up. Each week we publish online a summary of the material that we cover.

If your English is intermediate or better and you'd like a chance to engage in lively conversation, ask questions and maybe learn something new, then this session is for you.

If you are interested in beginners or improvers English, please let us know. We may set up other weekly sessions if there is sufficient demand.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Welcome to the Sunday group for intermediate italian level . This is a casual conversation group where people who want to improve their italian can come, chat and have a coffee (or another beverage, if you desire). We don't set topic or structure to the meeting aside from coming to the cafe and chatting about whatever's on your mind.

Advanced and native speakers are also welcome to come and help out. It should be noted that helpers are not expected to be teachers, however, if you have some questions I'm sure they will be more than willing to try to help you out.

Please be considerate to other members by keeping your RSVPs up to date and attending events when you indicate that you will.

If you're on the waiting list, please check your status in case you've been moved up to the Attendees list. <br>*** WARNING: pickpockets *** <br>Phones, laptops and wallets have been stolen in the Cafés in Down town . Gamla Stan , Down town and cafes are the paradise for pickpockets, so please watch your stuff (even in the pockets of your jackets that hang on your seat)! <br>**************

안녕하세요! :)

스웨덴에 거주중인 한국분들과 한국에 관심이 많은 스웨덴분들이 정기적으로 서로 만나 교류하고 스웨덴어/한국어를 연습할 수 있도록 언어교환 모임을 시작해보려고 합니다. 본 모임에서 언어수업 등을 제공하는 것은 아니나, 새로운 사람을 만나 이야기 나누것을 좋아하는 분, 스웨덴어를 연습하고자 하는 분은 모두 환영입니다. 각 레벨에 맞는 대화 파트너를 찾아드릴 수 있게 신청시에 본인의 스웨덴어 레벨을 적어주세요.
그럼 모임에서 뵙겠습니다 :)

민정&오스발드 드림

description:
With Stockholm Language Exchange, improve your conversational language level and ability!

We have regular meetings set up for Swedish, English, French, Spanish, German, Russian, Portuguese, Italian, Finnish, Arabic, Chinese and Japanese and more languages to come.

Thanks to all our volunteers who give up their time to help - everybody can help out in his/her mother language - , the group became a wonderful language exchange.

Below you will have an idea of the schedule. This planning can change every week, please check the calendar to see the real events and to be able to sign in:

Monday: Japanese, Swedish <br> Tuesday: English <br> Wednesday: French, German, Russian, Finnish, Swedish <br> Thursday: Spanish <br> Sunday: French, Spanish, German, Italian, Portuguese, Arabic, Chinese, Swedish

Come and improve your fluency with help of native speakers, and take actively part of the group in helping yourself people who want to learn your language!

Swedish courses Stockholm

Andy your main organiser


Jonas Rognon - Co-organiser

Welcome to Stockholm Erlang Meetup - situated in Erlang Valley in Sweden, where Erlang was invented.

About this group

Founded in 2012, this community is devoted to the Erlang Ecosystem and promoting anything on the BEAM. Are you Erlang curious? You are welcome!

About Erlang

Erlang is a functional programming language created at Ericsson, and designed to build massive, distributed, resilient, scalable software. The Erlang ecosystem contains a range of supported languages (Erlang, Efene, Lua, Prolog, Elixir, LFE ...) which interact seamlessly with the OTP libraries and the BEAM VM.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
La French connexion de Stockholm regroupe les Français, francophones et francophiles habitant le grand Stockholm. Nous organisons régulièrement des rencontres, à raison d’un ”fika” dans l’après-midi chaque premier samedi du mois et un afterwork en soirée en milieu de mois. Les rencontres se font en général dans des cafés ou des bars. Il arrive que nous organisions des événements plus ponctuels (repas de Noël, tournoi de ”kubb”, excursions dans l’archipel, ou à Uppsala pour rencontrer les Français uppsaliens).


Le groupe existe depuis de nombreuses années sur le forum Photo-Suède et le groupe meetup a été créé pour faciliter l’organisation des événements. Le but du groupe est de faire se rencontrer des nouveaux venus et des ”vétérans” pour échanger sur la vie en Suède. Nous ne proposons pas d’introduction formelle, la vie de ce groupe est basée sur le volontariat, la disponibilité et la participation de tout un chacun. Les administrateurs vous encouragent tous à participer aux rencontres mais n’hésitez pas non plus à proposer vous-mêmes des activités. Les nouvelles idées sont toujours les bienvenues !

Si vous souhaitez participer à un évenement, inscrivez-vous en répondant ”Oui” et essayez de venir au rendez-vous à peu près à l’heure. Ceux qui répondent ”Peut-être” sont conviés à confirmer dès que possible s’ils viennent ou non. C’est toujours plus facile de planifier quand on sait à peu près combien de personnes vont venir. Ce sont des règles de convivialité simples, merci de les respecter ! Bienvenue à tous à la French connection !
name: French Connection Stockholm

description:
Hi!
The association Un Petit Coin de France has been founded in 2008 by a group od friends playing card games in the basement of the Stockolm's reformed church. Six years later, the association has grown a lot.
Our goal today is to share good times all year long around the French and Swedish cultures and traditions. This year, many events are scheduled: musical quiz, tastings of French and Swedish products, a Beaujolais evening and many other surprises...
For those who loves sports, it is also possible to join one of our team (innebandy or touch). For more information please check the Facebook page (https://www.facebook.com/UnPetitCoinDeFrance/).

The annual fee to be a member of the association is 100 sek and gives you access to all the activities (evenings and trainings).

Welcome!

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hej,

Vad kul att ni är intresserad av vår språkgrupp!

Den här gruppen är till för alla som vill mötas och konversera på japanska och svenska. Alla som kan hålla en konversation på grund-/medelnivå är välkomna. Är ditt modersmål svenska eller japanska och du är intresserad av att lära dig ett av språken är du också välkommen. Nybörjare i båda språken är såklart också välkomna i mån av plats (skicka ett meddelande innan du blir medlem om du är osäker på din nivå).

Vi talar japanska i en timme och sedan byter vi till svenska den återstående timmen.

☆Schema

18:00〜19:00 Japanska

19:00〜20:00 Svenska

Har ni några synpunkter, idéer eller andra förslag skicka gärna ett meddelande så löser vi det.

Vi ses snart~

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br> <br>こんにちは、

このグループの目的は、日本語とスウェーデン語で語学交換することです。参加対象は、日本語ネイティヴ、スウェーデン語ネイティヴもしくは、日本語かスウェーデン語を 中級レベルで会話できる方です。 

 もちろん、スウェーデン語初心者もしくは日本語初心者の方も大歓迎です。

毎週カフェやバーに集まり、1時間日本語を話し、残りの1時間はスウェーデン語に切り替えます。

開催場所は固定ではありません。みんなで行ってみたいカフェやバーがあればどんどん教えてください。語学交換以外にも、一緒に料理をするだとか博物館に行くといった文化交流イベントも大歓迎です。みんなでやってみたいことがあれば、どしどし提案してください。

また、そのほか質問や改善点があれば遠慮なく言ってください。

みなさんが、来てよかったな〜来週も来たいな！と思えるようなミートアップグループにできるよう一緒に頑張りましょうね。

☆スケジュール

18：00〜19：00日本語

19：00〜20：00スウェーデン語

それではまた。

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br>

Hello,

How great that you're interested in our meetup group! <br>

The aim of this group is to converse in Japanese and Swedish. Everybody who can hold a conversation at an intermediate level is welcome to this meetup. If your mother tongue is Japanese or Swedish and you're interested in learning the other language, you're welcome to join as well. Beginners in both languages are also welcome based on how many spots are available (if you're uncertain about your current level send us a message before applying to the group). <br>

We speak Japanese for 1 hour and then we switch to Swedish for the remaining hour.

☆Schedule

18:00〜19:00 Japanese

19:00〜20:00 Swedish

If you have any viewpoints, ideas or other proposals please send a message and we'll try to incorporate it. <br>

See you there~ <br>
name: Speak Japanese and Swedish/Prata japanska och svenska

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Obs! Den här gruppen tar en paus för tillfället då jag är i Thailand. Jag är tillbaka i juni 2018 :)

Sawadii khap!

Thailändska ska man förstås helst lära sig från någon som har thailändska som modersmål, men ibland kan det vara värdefullt att också diskutera språket med någon som har ett svenskt perspektiv. Någon som redan har gått igenom samma inlärningsprocess i vuxen ålder och kan dela med sig av sina erfarenheter.

Denna meetup-grupp är till för dig som vill lära dig de absoluta grunderna i thailändska. Vilka ljud finns i thailändska som vi inte har i svenska språket? Hur fungerar det thailändska skriftspråket och är det värt att lära sig det? Vilka ord och fraser är viktigast att lära sig först?

Jag som har skapat gruppen har åkt till Thailand regelbundet i över 10 år. Jag kan inte thailändska flytande, men jag behärskar grunderna väldigt bra. Lektionerna är gratis och är något som jag tänker mig att vi utformar lite tillsammans utifrån vad deltagarna har för önskemål. Likaså skulle jag vilja ha förslag på var vi kan hålla till. Jag är van vid att ha meetups på restauranger och caféer, men det är viktigt att man kan sitta lite separat så man inte stör de andra gästerna.

/Adam
name: Thailändska för nybörjare
organizer.name: Adam Nybäck

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hallo alle zusammen und herzlich willkommen auf den Stockholm German Meetup!
Das Ziel dieses Meetup ist Konversation auf Deutsch zu betreiben, um unsere Sprachkenntnisse zu verbessern. Selbstverständlich sind deutsche Muttersprachler auch willkommen :)

Wer bin ich? Ich komme aus Italien aber wohne in Stockholm seit fast einem Jahr. Ich arbeite im Vertrieb und habe vorher mit deutschen Kunden gearbeitet. Ich habe German Meetups in Budapest und Dublin organisiert. Ich arbeite echt viel unter der Woche, deswegen habe ich mich entscheidet, ein Meetup am Wochenende zu organisieren.
Vorher konnte ich Deutsch fliessend sprechen, jetzt muss ich es aber aufpolieren :)

Alle, die genug Deutsch kennen, um ein bisschen Konversation zu machen, sind einfach willkommen.

LG,

Stefania

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
To know if you should join, you need to know the reason for why I started this group: I’m a Swedish/Indian woman who spent most my life in international and expatriate surroundings. I’m since 3 years back in my beloved hometown, but at the same time lost. I’m in a steady relationship but not interested in family-life (children)... or the next night out for that matter (although very appreciated now and then). I want to find other women with some kind of connection to Scandinavia, who also are “stuck” between social cultures (returned Swedish expats, foreign parents but Swedish themselves, moved to Sweden and changed citizenship, you get the idea), who together with me want to find more people who we can laugh, explore, and enjoy some of our free time with.

What makes this group a little different is that everyone is made into an Event Organiser, and thereby can, if they want to, create their own "event" or activity. The level of effort and prestige the event is worth is decided by each Even Organiser. For myself it's zero prestige and minimum effort and so far I've had loads of fun with it!
name: Scandinavian women with expat/foreign backgrounds

Welcome to all those who are interested in practising English conversation and improving English language skills!

Currently we have one weekly session to practise speaking English at an intermediate level. We discuss general topics but have some emphasis on learning and discussing new words, phrases and idioms as they come up. Each week we publish online a summary of the material that we cover.

If your English is intermediate or better and you'd like a chance to engage in lively conversation, ask questions and maybe learn something new, then this session is for you.

If you are interested in beginners or improvers English, please let us know. We may set up other weekly sessions if there is sufficient demand.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Welcome to the Sunday group for intermediate italian level . This is a casual conversation group where people who want to improve their italian can come, chat and have a coffee (or another beverage, if you desire). We don't set topic or structure to the meeting aside from coming to the cafe and chatting about whatever's on your mind.

Advanced and native speakers are also welcome to come and help out. It should be noted that helpers are not expected to be teachers, however, if you have some questions I'm sure they will be more than willing to try to help you out.

Please be considerate to other members by keeping your RSVPs up to date and attending events when you indicate that you will.

If you're on the waiting list, please check your status in case you've been moved up to the Attendees list. <br>*** WARNING: pickpockets *** <br>Phones, laptops and wallets have been stolen in the Cafés in Down town . Hej alla koreaintresserade! :)

Målet med den här gruppen är att bli en mötesplats för koreaintresserad svenskar och inflyttade koreaner som vill träffas och mingla och samtidigt öva på svenska/koreanska. Vi har inga planerade lektioner eller likande, utan vi träffas och fikar och pratar helt enkelt.

Alla nivåer är välkomna. Skriv bara vilken nivå du är på så att vi kan hitta någon som passar bra till din språknivå. Vi ses!

Minjeong & Osvald

(This group is mainly for people who are fluent in either Swedish or Korean to get a good language exchange.)

안녕하세요! :)

스웨덴에 거주중인 한국분들과 한국에 관심이 많은 스웨덴분들이 정기적으로 서로 만나 교류하고 스웨덴어/한국어를 연습할 수 있도록 언어교환 모임을 시작해보려고 합니다. 본 모임에서 언어수업 등을 제공하는 것은 아니나, 새로운 사람을 만나 이야기 나누것을 좋아하는 분, 스웨덴어를 연습하고자 하는 분은 모두 환영입니다. 각 레벨에 맞는 대화 파트너를 찾아드릴 수 있게 신청시에 본인의 스웨덴어 레벨을 적어주세요.
그럼 모임에서 뵙겠습니다 :)

민정&오스발드 드림

With Stockholm Language Exchange, improve your conversational language level and ability!

We have regular meetings set up for Swedish, English, French, Spanish, German, Russian, Portuguese, Italian, Finnish, Arabic, Chinese and Japanese and more languages to come.

Thanks to all our volunteers who give up their time to help - everybody can help out in his/her mother language - , the group became a wonderful language exchange.

Below you will have an idea of the schedule. This planning can change every week, please check the calendar to see the real events and to be able to sign in:

Monday: Japanese, Swedish <br> Tuesday: English <br> Wednesday: French, German, Russian, Finnish, Swedish <br> Thursday: Spanish <br> Sunday: French, Spanish, German, Italian, Portuguese, Arabic, Chinese, Swedish

Come and improve your fluency with help of native speakers, and take actively part of the group in helping yourself people who want to learn your language!

Swedish courses Stockholm

Andy your main organiser


Jonas Rognon - Co-organiser

description:
Welcome to Stockholm Erlang Meetup - situated in Erlang Valley in Sweden, where Erlang was invented.

About this group

Founded in 2012, this community is devoted to the Erlang Ecosystem and promoting anything on the BEAM. Are you Erlang curious? You are welcome!

About Erlang

Erlang is a functional programming language created at Ericsson, and designed to build massive, distributed, resilient, scalable software. The Erlang ecosystem contains a range of supported languages (Erlang, Efene, Lua, Prolog, Elixir, LFE ...) which interact seamlessly with the OTP libraries and the BEAM VM.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
La French connexion de Stockholm regroupe les Français, francophones et francophiles habitant le grand Stockholm. Nous organisons régulièrement des rencontres, à raison d’un ”fika” dans l’après-midi chaque premier samedi du mois et un afterwork en soirée en milieu de mois. Les rencontres se font en général dans des cafés ou des bars. Il arrive que nous organisions des événements plus ponctuels (repas de Noël, tournoi de ”kubb”, excursions dans l’archipel, ou à Uppsala pour rencontrer les Français uppsaliens).


Le groupe existe depuis de nombreuses années sur le forum Photo-Suède et le groupe meetup a été créé pour faciliter l’organisation des événements. Le but du groupe est de faire se rencontrer des nouveaux venus et des ”vétérans” pour échanger sur la vie en Suède. Nous ne proposons pas d’introduction formelle, la vie de ce groupe est basée sur le volontariat, la disponibilité et la participation de tout un chacun. Les administrateurs vous encouragent tous à participer aux rencontres mais n’hésitez pas non plus à proposer vous-mêmes des activités. Les nouvelles idées sont toujours les bienvenues !

Si vous souhaitez participer à un évenement, inscrivez-vous en répondant ”Oui” et essayez de venir au rendez-vous à peu près à l’heure. Ceux qui répondent ”Peut-être” sont conviés à confirmer dès que possible s’ils viennent ou non. C’est toujours plus facile de planifier quand on sait à peu près combien de personnes vont venir. Ce sont des règles de convivialité simples, merci de les respecter ! Bienvenue à tous à la French connection !
name: French Connection Stockholm

description:
Hi!
The association Un Petit Coin de France has been founded in 2008 by a group od friends playing card games in the basement of the Stockolm's reformed church. Six years later, the association has grown a lot.
Our goal today is to share good times all year long around the French and Swedish cultures and traditions. This year, many events are scheduled: musical quiz, tastings of French and Swedish products, a Beaujolais evening and many other surprises...
For those who loves sports, it is also possible to join one of our team (innebandy or touch). For more information please check the Facebook page (https://www.facebook.com/UnPetitCoinDeFrance/).

The annual fee to be a member of the association is 100 sek and gives you access to all the activities (evenings and trainings).

Welcome!

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hej,

Vad kul att ni är intresserad av vår språkgrupp!

Den här gruppen är till för alla som vill mötas och konversera på japanska och svenska. Alla som kan hålla en konversation på grund-/medelnivå är välkomna. Är ditt modersmål svenska eller japanska och du är intresserad av att lära dig ett av språken är du också välkommen. Nybörjare i båda språken är såklart också välkomna i mån av plats (skicka ett meddelande innan du blir medlem om du är osäker på din nivå).

Vi talar japanska i en timme och sedan byter vi till svenska den återstående timmen.

☆Schema

18:00〜19:00 Japanska

19:00〜20:00 Svenska

Har ni några synpunkter, idéer eller andra förslag skicka gärna ett meddelande så löser vi det.

Vi ses snart~

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br> <br>こんにちは、

このグループの目的は、日本語とスウェーデン語で語学交換することです。参加対象は、日本語ネイティヴ、スウェーデン語ネイティヴもしくは、日本語かスウェーデン語を 中級レベルで会話できる方です。 

 もちろん、スウェーデン語初心者もしくは日本語初心者の方も大歓迎です。

毎週カフェやバーに集まり、1時間日本語を話し、残りの1時間はスウェーデン語に切り替えます。

開催場所は固定ではありません。みんなで行ってみたいカフェやバーがあればどんどん教えてください。語学交換以外にも、一緒に料理をするだとか博物館に行くといった文化交流イベントも大歓迎です。みんなでやってみたいことがあれば、どしどし提案してください。

また、そのほか質問や改善点があれば遠慮なく言ってください。

みなさんが、来てよかったな〜来週も来たいな！と思えるようなミートアップグループにできるよう一緒に頑張りましょうね。

☆スケジュール

18：00〜19：00日本語

19：00〜20：00スウェーデン語

それではまた。

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br>

Hello,

How great that you're interested in our meetup group! <br>

The aim of this group is to converse in Japanese and Swedish. Everybody who can hold a conversation at an intermediate level is welcome to this meetup. If your mother tongue is Japanese or Swedish and you're interested in learning the other language, you're welcome to join as well. Beginners in both languages are also welcome based on how many spots are available (if you're uncertain about your current level send us a message before applying to the group). <br>

We speak Japanese for 1 hour and then we switch to Swedish for the remaining hour.

☆Schedule

18:00〜19:00 Japanese

19:00〜20:00 Swedish

If you have any viewpoints, ideas or other proposals please send a message and we'll try to incorporate it. <br>

See you there~ <br>

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Obs! Den här gruppen tar en paus för tillfället då jag är i Thailand. Jag är tillbaka i juni 2018 :)

Sawadii khap!

Thailändska ska man förstås helst lära sig från någon som har thailändska som modersmål, men ibland kan det vara värdefullt att också diskutera språket med någon som har ett svenskt perspektiv. Någon som redan har gått igenom samma inlärningsprocess i vuxen ålder och kan dela med sig av sina erfarenheter.

Denna meetup-grupp är till för dig som vill lära dig de absoluta grunderna i thailändska. Vilka ljud finns i thailändska som vi inte har i svenska språket? Hur fungerar det thailändska skriftspråket och är det värt att lära sig det? Vilka ord och fraser är viktigast att lära sig först?

Jag som har skapat gruppen har åkt till Thailand regelbundet i över 10 år. Jag kan inte thailändska flytande, men jag behärskar grunderna väldigt bra. Lektionerna är gratis och är något som jag tänker mig att vi utformar lite tillsammans utifrån vad deltagarna har för önskemål. Likaså skulle jag vilja ha förslag på var vi kan hålla till. Jag är van vid att ha meetups på restauranger och caféer, men det är viktigt att man kan sitta lite separat så man inte stör de andra gästerna.

/Adam
name: Thailändska för nybörjare
organizer.name: Adam Nybäck

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hallo alle zusammen und herzlich willkommen auf den Stockholm German Meetup!
Das Ziel dieses Meetup ist Konversation auf Deutsch zu betreiben, um unsere Sprachkenntnisse zu verbessern. Selbstverständlich sind deutsche Muttersprachler auch willkommen :)

Wer bin ich? Ich komme aus Italien aber wohne in Stockholm seit fast einem Jahr. Ich arbeite im Vertrieb und habe vorher mit deutschen Kunden gearbeitet. Ich habe German Meetups in Budapest und Dublin organisiert. Ich arbeite echt viel unter der Woche, deswegen habe ich mich entscheidet, ein Meetup am Wochenende zu organisieren.
Vorher konnte ich Deutsch fliessend sprechen, jetzt muss ich es aber aufpolieren :)

Alle, die genug Deutsch kennen, um ein bisschen Konversation zu machen, sind einfach willkommen.

LG,

Stefania

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
To know if you should join, you need to know the reason for why I started this group: I’m a Swedish/Indian woman who spent most my life in international and expatriate surroundings. I’m since 3 years back in my beloved hometown, but at the same time lost. I’m in a steady relationship but not interested in family-life (children)... or the next night out for that matter (although very appreciated now and then). I want to find other women with some kind of connection to Scandinavia, who also are “stuck” between social cultures (returned Swedish expats, foreign parents but Swedish themselves, moved to Sweden and changed citizenship, you get the idea), who together with me want to find more people who we can laugh, explore, and enjoy some of our free time with.

What makes this group a little different is that everyone is made into an Event Organiser, and thereby can, if they want to, create their own "event" or activity. The level of effort and prestige the event is worth is decided by each Even Organiser. For myself it's zero prestige and minimum effort and so far I've had loads of fun with it!
name: Scandinavian women with expat/foreign backgrounds

description:
Welcome to all those who are interested in practising English conversation and improving English language skills!

Currently we have one weekly session to practise speaking English at an intermediate level. We discuss general topics but have some emphasis on learning and discussing new words, phrases and idioms as they come up. Each week we publish online a summary of the material that we cover.

If your English is intermediate or better and you'd like a chance to engage in lively conversation, ask questions and maybe learn something new, then this session is for you.

If you are interested in beginners or improvers English, please let us know. We may set up other weekly sessions if there is sufficient demand.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Welcome to the Sunday group for intermediate italian level . This is a casual conversation group where people who want to improve their italian can come, chat and have a coffee (or another beverage, if you desire). We don't set topic or structure to the meeting aside from coming to the cafe and chatting about whatever's on your mind.

Advanced and native speakers are also welcome to come and help out. It should be noted that helpers are not expected to be teachers, however, if you have some questions I'm sure they will be more than willing to try to help you out.

Please be considerate to other members by keeping your RSVPs up to date and attending events when you indicate that you will.

If you're on the waiting list, please check your status in case you've been moved up to the Attendees list. <br>*** WARNING: pickpockets *** <br>Phones, laptops and wallets have been stolen in the Cafés in Down town . Gamla Stan , Down town and cafes are the paradise for pickpockets, so please watch your stuff (even in the pockets of your jackets that hang on your seat)! <br>**************
name: Excel in Italiano! meet in Café 60, Sveavägen!

description:
Hej alla koreaintresserade! :)

Målet med den här gruppen är att bli en mötesplats för koreaintresserad svenskar och inflyttade koreaner som vill träffas och mingla och samtidigt öva på svenska/koreanska. Vi har inga planerade lektioner eller likande, utan vi träffas och fikar och pratar helt enkelt.

Alla nivåer är välkomna. Skriv bara vilken nivå du är på så att vi kan hitta någon som passar bra till din språknivå. Vi ses!

Minjeong & Osvald

(This group is mainly for people who are fluent in either Swedish or Korean to get a good language exchange.)

안녕하세요! :)

스웨덴에 거주중인 한국분들과 한국에 관심이 많은 스웨덴분들이 정기적으로 서로 만나 교류하고 스웨덴어/한국어를 연습할 수 있도록 언어교환 모임을 시작해보려고 합니다. 본 모임에서 언어수업 등을 제공하는 것은 아니나, 새로운 사람을 만나 이야기 나누것을 좋아하는 분, 스웨덴어를 연습하고자 하는 분은 모두 환영입니다. 각 레벨에 맞는 대화 파트너를 찾아드릴 수 있게 신청시에 본인의 스웨덴어 레벨을 적어주세요.
그럼 모임에서 뵙겠습니다 :)

민정&오스발드 드림
name: Koreansk-svensk fika/스웨덴어-한국어 언어교환모임

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
With Stockholm Language Exchange, improve your conversational language level and ability!

We have regular meetings set up for Swedish, English, French, Spanish, German, Russian, Portuguese, Italian, Finnish, Arabic, Chinese and Japanese and more languages to come.

Thanks to all our volunteers who give up their time to help - everybody can help out in his/her mother language - , the group became a wonderful language exchange.

Below you will have an idea of the schedule. This planning can change every week, please check the calendar to see the real events and to be able to sign in:

Monday: Japanese, Swedish <br> Tuesday: English <br> Wednesday: French, German, Russian, Finnish, Swedish <br> Thursday: Spanish <br> Sunday: French, Spanish, German, Italian, Portuguese, Arabic, Chinese, Swedish

Come and improve your fluency with help of native speakers, and take actively part of the group in helping yourself people who want to learn your language!

Swedish courses Stockholm

Andy your main organiser


Jonas Rognon - Co-organiser

These could be comedy shows, festivals, concerts, cinema premiers, opening night events, dancing and cultural events, all within our great city of Stockholm.

If you like to have fun, meet new people and make friends, you belong right here.

The groups motto is to enjoy Stockholm and every great thing about it, sharing that joy with other friends, old and new.

description:
Welcome to Stockholm Erlang Meetup - situated in Erlang Valley in Sweden, where Erlang was invented.

About this group

Founded in 2012, this community is devoted to the Erlang Ecosystem and promoting anything on the BEAM. Are you Erlang curious? You are welcome!

About Erlang

Erlang is a functional programming language created at Ericsson, and designed to build massive, distributed, resilient, scalable software. The Erlang ecosystem contains a range of supported languages (Erlang, Efene, Lua, Prolog, Elixir, LFE ...) which interact seamlessly with the OTP libraries and the BEAM VM.

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
La French connexion de Stockholm regroupe les Français, francophones et francophiles habitant le grand Stockholm. Nous organisons régulièrement des rencontres, à raison d’un ”fika” dans l’après-midi chaque premier samedi du mois et un afterwork en soirée en milieu de mois. Les rencontres se font en général dans des cafés ou des bars. Il arrive que nous organisions des événements plus ponctuels (repas de Noël, tournoi de ”kubb”, excursions dans l’archipel, ou à Uppsala pour rencontrer les Français uppsaliens).


Le groupe existe depuis de nombreuses années sur le forum Photo-Suède et le groupe meetup a été créé pour faciliter l’organisation des événements. Le but du groupe est de faire se rencontrer des nouveaux venus et des ”vétérans” pour échanger sur la vie en Suède. Nous ne proposons pas d’introduction formelle, la vie de ce groupe est basée sur le volontariat, la disponibilité et la participation de tout un chacun. Les administrateurs vous encouragent tous à participer aux rencontres mais n’hésitez pas non plus à proposer vous-mêmes des activités. Les nouvelles idées sont toujours les bienvenues !

Si vous souhaitez participer à un évenement, inscrivez-vous en répondant ”Oui” et essayez de venir au rendez-vous à peu près à l’heure. Ceux qui répondent ”Peut-être” sont conviés à confirmer dès que possible s’ils viennent ou non. C’est toujours plus facile de planifier quand on sait à peu près combien de personnes vont venir. Ce sont des règles de convivialité simples, merci de les respecter ! Bienvenue à tous à la French connection !
name: French Connection Stockholm

description:
Hi!
The association Un Petit Coin de France has been founded in 2008 by a group od friends playing card games in the basement of the Stockolm's reformed church. Six years later, the association has grown a lot.
Our goal today is to share good times all year long around the French and Swedish cultures and traditions. This year, many events are scheduled: musical quiz, tastings of French and Swedish products, a Beaujolais evening and many other surprises...
For those who loves sports, it is also possible to join one of our team (innebandy or touch). For more information please check the Facebook page (https://www.facebook.com/UnPetitCoinDeFrance/).

The annual fee to be a member of the association is 100 sek and gives you access to all the activities (evenings and trainings).

Welcome!

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Hej,

Vad kul att ni är intresserad av vår språkgrupp!

Den här gruppen är till för alla som vill mötas och konversera på japanska och svenska. Alla som kan hålla en konversation på grund-/medelnivå är välkomna. Är ditt modersmål svenska eller japanska och du är intresserad av att lära dig ett av språken är du också välkommen. Nybörjare i båda språken är såklart också välkomna i mån av plats (skicka ett meddelande innan du blir medlem om du är osäker på din nivå).

Vi talar japanska i en timme och sedan byter vi till svenska den återstående timmen.

☆Schema

18:00〜19:00 Japanska

19:00〜20:00 Svenska

Har ni några synpunkter, idéer eller andra förslag skicka gärna ett meddelande så löser vi det.

Vi ses snart~

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br> <br>こんにちは、

このグループの目的は、日本語とスウェーデン語で語学交換することです。参加対象は、日本語ネイティヴ、スウェーデン語ネイティヴもしくは、日本語かスウェーデン語を 中級レベルで会話できる方です。 

 もちろん、スウェーデン語初心者もしくは日本語初心者の方も大歓迎です。

毎週カフェやバーに集まり、1時間日本語を話し、残りの1時間はスウェーデン語に切り替えます。

開催場所は固定ではありません。みんなで行ってみたいカフェやバーがあればどんどん教えてください。語学交換以外にも、一緒に料理をするだとか博物館に行くといった文化交流イベントも大歓迎です。みんなでやってみたいことがあれば、どしどし提案してください。

また、そのほか質問や改善点があれば遠慮なく言ってください。

みなさんが、来てよかったな〜来週も来たいな！と思えるようなミートアップグループにできるよう一緒に頑張りましょうね。

☆スケジュール

18：00〜19：00日本語

19：00〜20：00スウェーデン語

それではまた。

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- <br>

Hello,

How great that you're interested in our meetup group! <br>

The aim of this group is to converse in Japanese and Swedish. Everybody who can hold a conversation at an intermediate level is welcome to this meetup. If your mother tongue is Japanese or Swedish and you're interested in learning the other language, you're welcome to join as well. Beginners in both languages are also welcome based on how many spots are available (if you're uncertain about your current level send us a message before applying to the group). <br>

We speak Japanese for 1 hour and then we switch to Swedish for the remaining hour.

☆Schedule

18:00〜19:00 Japanese

19:00〜20:00 Swedish

If you have any viewpoints, ideas or other proposals please send a message and we'll try to incorporate it. <br>

See you there~ <br>

category.name: language/ethnic identity
description:
Obs! Den här gruppen tar en paus för tillfället då jag är i Thailand. Jag är tillbaka i juni 2018 :)

Sawadii khap!

Thailändska ska man förstås helst lära sig från någon som har thailändska som modersmål, men ibland kan det vara värdefullt att också diskutera språket med någon som har ett svenskt perspektiv. Någon som redan har gått igenom samma inlärningsprocess i vuxen ålder och kan dela med sig av sina erfarenheter.

Denna meetup-grupp är till för dig som vill lära dig de absoluta grunderna i thailändska. Vilka ljud finns i thailändska som vi inte har i svenska språket? Hur fungerar det thailändska skriftspråket och är det värt att lära sig det? Vilka ord och fraser är viktigast att lära sig först?

Jag som har skapat gruppen har åkt till Thailand regelbundet i över 10 år. Jag kan inte thailändska flytande, men jag behärskar grunderna väldigt bra. Lektionerna är gratis och är något som jag tänker mig att vi utformar lite tillsammans utifrån vad deltagarna har för önskemål. Likaså skulle jag vilja ha förslag på var vi kan hålla till. Jag är van vid att ha meetups på restauranger och caféer, men det är viktigt att man kan sitta lite separat så man inte stör de andra gästerna.

/Adam
name: Thailändska för nybörjare
